data.description: Price Modified! This property consists of multiple properties combined for tax purposes & can be returned to original status (see survey) & very easily made into three waterfront (no water view) properties. A buyer could split & sell the buildable side lots that are already 90% cleared & filled, or just keep it as one private property as the current owner has chosen to do for the past 18 yrs. Even though there is a private trail that leads to the adjacent community pier, a buyer can elect to build their own pier, dock, boathouse, lift, etc. as desired. In fact, each of the three lots could have private piers/docks. Pelican Bayou is 10-12ft deep at this location & can easily support a boat up to 30ft long. By boat, you can be in the Blackwater River in 2 minutes, Blackwater Bay in 5 minutes, & even the Gulf of Mexico in approximately 40minutes! In the heart of Milton close to I10 is this truly exceptional bayou-front property encompassing 6.5 acres of unparalleled natural beauty. As you step onto the grounds, you'll be captivated by the panoramic views of mature trees, where each day is adorned with the peaceful sounds of nature. The home seamlessly integrates modern sophistication with timeless elegance & the expansive windows bathe the living spaces in natural light. The large kitchen was renovated with granite counters, stainless appliance & the painted cabinets. The main suite features 2 walk-in closets, jetted tub, huge shower & double vanity cabinets. With a split bedroom plan adorned with high ceilings and crown molding, numerous well-appointed bedrooms, & inviting indoor-outdoor areas, this home is built for comfort and entertainment. The Sunroom overlooks the large in-ground, salt-water, screened pool area, where you will undoubtedly spend most of your time. Then well manicured landscape with irrigation, horseshoe pit, a variety of fruit & palm trees & plenty of room for an additional building or perhaps a private tennis court.  Possible Assummable Mortgage.
